All Progressives Congress (APC) stalwart Asiwaju Bola Tinubu has congratulated the Otun Olubadan of Ibadan, Lekan Balogun, on his designation as the Olubadan-in-waiting. In a congratulatory message yesterday by his media aide Tunde Rahman, the one-time Lagos governor urged in-coming Olubadan to promote peace and stability. Describing the appointment as an elevation to the zenith of leadership institution in the land, Tinubu expressed hope that the new Olubadan  would deploy his tremendous skills and rich understanding of the traditional institution to promote peace and stability in Ibadan Land, Oyo state and Nigeria as a whole. The statement reads: “The beauty of the rich and highly-respected traditional hierarchical leadership structure of Ibadanland has again affirmed itself.   Court fixes March 25 for verdict on $418m Paris Club debt…     Ekiti, Osun polls: INEC insists on BVAS despite glitches     Aregbesola’s thugs fired gunshots without provocation, say…   - Advertisement - “As a former senator and the Otun Olubadan until this new appointment, you have truly earned your stripes. - Advertisement - “Your high leadership qualities, particularly your tremendous skills, experience, knowledge and deep understanding of traditional institution are worthy of note. “As the 42nd Olubadan of Ibadanland, l hope and pray that you will deploy these qualities to promote peace, unity and stability not only in Ibadanland, Oyo state, Yorubaland but also across the country.” The APC chieftain prayed for a long and eventful reign for the new Olubadan. SPONSORED